    "Opportunities (Ref)": "/Opportunities/10064",
    "Commitment": "2-4 hours/week",
    "Description": "<p class=\"p3\">The Volunteer Engineering Experience Program is a University of Toronto Engineering not for profit which gives engineering students a unique opportunity the chance to complete technical projects with Toronto Not for Profits. We are a rapidly growing organization with a diverse roster of not-for-profit organizations (e.g. Sick Kids, Canadian Urban Institute, Toronto Atmospheric Fund), and we have helped hundreds of students who have gained tremendous pro-bono experience.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nWe are always looking for professionals to offer some time to work with and mentor students working on projects in VEEP (this could be anything from working with our operations team to facilitate workshops to meeting with students for a couple of hours a month to review their project progress and challenge their thinking). Throughout this experience, you will have the opportunity to not only help our students develop as young engineers and leaders, but also to help the great work that Toronto not-for-profits are doing for the community.</p>\n\n<p class=\"p3\"><span class=\"wixGuard\">​</span></p>\n\n<p class=\"p3\">If you would like more information on VEEPs Program, here is a link to our program overview deck:<br />\n<a href=\"https://drive.google.com/file/d/1L7CXcthU2V_PJ55Ln6MSxBMuShX5b4Qv/view?usp=sharing\">https://drive.google.com/file/d/1L7CXcthU2V_PJ55Ln6MSxBMuShX5b4Qv/view?usp=sharing</a></p>",
    "Website": "",
