    "Opportunities (Ref)": "/Opportunities/10032",
    "Commitment": "1 - 2 hrs/month",
    "Description": "<p class=\"p3\">The goal of the YES Mentorship Program&nbsp; is to connect YES clients to Industry Leaders (expert mentors) in order to build capacity, employability, networks and foster entrepreneurship in young people through establishing supportive, caring and trusting relationships with mentors.&nbsp; At Youth Employment Services YES, our clients often request mentorship opportunities with those who are currently established in the workforce as they feel/know that having a career mentor to whom they can ask questions to about the job search, entering the job market, and about planning their own career path can be extremely valuable to them.<br />\nAs an Industry Leader (mentor), you would:</p>\n\n<p class=\"p3\"><br />\n- Have over 5 years of professional work experience<br />\n- Develop caring, nurturing and supportive relationships with at risk youth as they join the workforce<br />\n- Be a caring adult and positive role model encouraging and coaching mentees to meet their career goals<br />\n- Work collaboratively with the YES Coordinator to provide critical feedback informing ongoing engagement with mentees<br />\n- Create a Mentor Profile on the YES Mentorship Hub.<br />\n- Learn best practices on being a mentor.<br />\n- Receive a monthly match with a youth who we think you would be a great mentor for and begin a personalized mentoring relationship that works for you and your schedule.<br />\n- Participate in our screening process (emails, phone calls and in-person meetings)<br />\n- Receive a Vulnerable Sector Search Police Reference Check Clearance<br />\n- Complete the AODA Customer Service Standard Module</p>\n\n<p class=\"p3\"><span class=\"wixGuard\">​</span></p>\n\n<p class=\"p3\">Youth Employment Services YES believes employment is empowerment and the cornerstone of safe and healthy communities, helping Toronto&#39;s marginalized and vulnerable youth find and maintain employment. YES is the employment champion for youth, an organization dedicated to changing lives forever. YES leads the Canadian youth sector with innovative programs, empowering disadvantaged youth to become self-sufficient members of society. &nbsp;</p>",
    "Website": "https://www.yes.on.ca/",
    "Application Instructions": "<p style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">All interested applicants please email YES Coordinator, Shari Raghoo at <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><a href=\"mailto:shari_raghoo@yes.on.ca\">shari_raghoo@yes.on.ca</a></span> or call at 416-504-5516 ex. 280</span></p>",
