    "Description": "<p class=\"p3\"><a href=\"http://veg.ca/\">Do you want more people in the GTA to learn about the benefits of a plant-based diet? Do you want to see more people sign up for the Veggie Challenge? And, do you have a car and a few hours to spare each month?<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nThen join our Set Up and Tear Down Crew for outreach events! Toronto is jam packed with events throughout the year and there&rsquo;s so many opportunities for the Toronto Vegetarian Association to be present. But we can only be there with the help of a driver to transport our materials to and from the TVA office to these great community events.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nWe&rsquo;re looking for new people to join our team and help out at an event or two each month. The role involves picking up materials from the TVA office at a time that&rsquo;s convenient for you, transporting them to the event on the actual day of the event and setting up the TVA table.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nAlternatively, it can be done in the reverse! You can do a tear down shift where you&rsquo;d pack up the materials at the end of an event, and bring them back to the TVA office at a time that&rsquo;s convenient for you.<br />\n&nbsp;<br />\nMembers of our set up and tear down crew receive a FREE TVA discount card, offering savings at over 115 veg-friendly businesses in the GTA.</a></p>\n\n<p class=\"p3\"><span class=\"wixGuard\">​</span></p>\n\n<p class=\"p3\">Qualifications and Application: You should be comfortable with heavy lifting, including up and down a flight of stairs, and must be willing to use your own vehicle for the role. Please email <a href=\"mailto:blazarus@veg.ca\">Barbi Lazarus</a> with the subject Set Up and Tear Down Team.</p>",
