    "Opportunities (Ref)": "/Opportunities/10056",
    "Commitment": "2-4 hours/week",
    "Description": "<p class=\"p3\">Are you a passionate young food-lover that believes in the right to healthy, nutritious food for every Canadian? Do you want to make a difference in your community and help everyone connect through the power of good food? Become a member of Community Food Centres Canada (CFCC) Young Professional Association (YPA) and become a&nbsp; leader in the good food movement today!<br />\n<br />\nCommunity Food Centres Canada (CFCC) is a dynamic national nonprofit working to create real change in the lives of low-income Canadians through the power of food. Our food centres are built as beautiful, vibrant, inviting spaces for people of all ages and backgrounds to come together in our kitchens and gardens to access nutritious meals, learn new food skills, and connect with their community. The YPA plays an integral role in helping us to grow our centres nationally, while learning and networking to become leaders in creating social change for food rights.</p>\n\n<p class=\"p3\"><span class=\"wixGuard\">​</span></p>\n\n<p class=\"p3\">YPA members meet regularly and enjoy many exclusive benefits including:<br />\n- Opportunities to network with like minded young professionals and good food<br />\n&nbsp;&nbsp; leaders<br />\n- Access to CFCC and exclusive partner events<br />\n- Hands on leadership and learning opportunities, with a specialized focus on social<br />\n&nbsp; advocacy, governance, project management, special events, and resource<br />\n&nbsp; development<br />\n- Developing meaningful connections to your community within the good food space<br />\n- See up close the impact of your charitable contributions on a National level</p>",
    "Website": "https://cfccanada.ca/en-US/",
    "Application Instructions": "<p style=\"font-size: 16px;\"><span style=\"font-size:16px;\">Interested in becoming a CFCC Young Professional Association member? Submit your letter of interest to CFCC Development Manager, Miranda McSorley, at <span style=\"text-decoration:underline\"><a href=\"mailto:miranda@cfccanada.ca\">miranda@cfccanada.ca</a></span> by June 11th, 2018. Thank you!</span></p>",
